                  </hi>. I live in Penton-street. On Saturday afternoon, at half-past one o'clock, I was in Edward Terrace, and saw the prisoner stand<lb></lb>ing just by Mr. Wetberall's gate—I went on to No. 4, and as I came back I saw the prisoner go from the door across the fields, to a person who was here—he took something from that person, and then he put this great coat on him—I followed him till he came to the station-house in Rosamond street, and there I gave him in charge.</p>
